Write programs demonstrating the use of the fork, clone, exec and its variants , wait ,exit system calls

SPOT EXERCISE

1. Demonstrate with a single C program with appropriate messages, the difference between cloned process and forked process. 

2. Write a C program to 

a. View the list of programs in current working directory (By the child process) - use appropriate exec variant.

b. Display the date. (By the parent process)

c. Also print the ids of parent and child processes using the respective functions.
